Friday Olokor, Abuja The Federal Executive Council on Wednesday approved N5.72bn for construction and consultancy services for the offices of the Nigeria Deposit Insurance Corporation. The Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Zainab Ahmed, briefed State House correspondents at the end of the meeting chaired by Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo at the State House, Abuja. She said that N3.23bn was approved for the construction of NDIC zonal office in Bauchi State. According to her, N2.49bn was approved for consultancy services for stage three work on NDIC corporate offices in Abuja and Lagos. “The corporation will be saving money and when the office accommodation is completed, it will provide comfortable and clean environment for the members of staff, boost their  morale as well as productivity. We have of course during these processes sought approvals from the BPP. “The second memo that was presented to council and was approved today is also in respect of the NDIC. It is for award of contracts for 12 consultancy services for the development of the NDIC corporate head office annex in Abuja, it’s office in Ikoyi, Lagos, as well as a training centre in Lekki, Lagos.” The Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika, said FEC approved N574m for insurance of College of Aviation in Zaria. He also said N271m was approved for the perimeter fencing of the Port Harcourt International Airport, which was abandoned since 2011. On the call to convert Arik Air into a national carrier rather than establishing a new one, Sirika said Arik Air was not suitable for a national carrier. Copyright PUNCH.
